AB  - The impact of conversion strategies on the value of convertible debt is examined. It is shown that, for capital structures comprised of multiple classes of convertible debt, the optimal conversion policy for a given bond class is affected by the decisions of other bond classes. Using this optimal conversion strategy, closed-form solutions for bond prices are derived.
